Pope Francis will name the first cardinals in February.
The Vatican announced Thursday that Pope Francis will name new cardinals of the Catholic Church for the first time on February 22.
Cardinals are the highest position in the clergy of the Catholic Church, second only to the pope, and they are the ones who elect the pope, so Francis will appoint his first group of men to help choose his successor.
