This trader, Richard Usher, left RBS in 2010 and is believed to have been relieved of his current position as European Chairman of Foreign Exchange Trading at JPMorgan.
Rohan Ramchandani, European head of cash trading at Citi, took a leave of absence this week, while Matt Gardiner, former head of foreign exchange trading at Barclays and UBS, was suspended by Standard Chartered this week.
None of these merchants have been charged with any offence.
Mr. Usher's group of instant messengers included bankers from Barclays and Citigroup, people familiar with the matter said.
